<h1>The CEU</h1>
<p>The Cooperative Elven Union - most commonly called The CEU - isn’t a country so much as it is a collection of different city states on Seishun that have long worked together. Although The CEU is known to be wary of non-elven political entities, it overall has a cooperative culture that’s welcoming of anyone.</p>

<p>Most of The CEU is found on a region along Seishun's western border known as Merchant's Coast. Although Merchant's Coast has a temperate environment that most would find pleasant, it borders a massive desert that the locals know to avoid. </p>

<h2 id="semdrali">Semdrali</h2>
<p>As the city-state lying on the eastern coast, Semdrali has had more exposure to <a asp-area="" asp-controller="Asha" asp-action="Vindral">Vindral</a> and <a asp-area="" asp-controller="Asha" asp-action="Kalshan">Kalshan</a> than either of the other two city states. While it remains distinctly elven in comparison to those two nations, Semdralians have a royal family with celestial heritage and other parts of foreign cultures have bled into their own. So whether someone is looking to leave or enter The CEU, Semdrali is often their first stop.</p>

<h3>Sights & Fashions</h3>
<p>Semdralians like to wear breathable clothes with layers, which is normally made out of materials like cotton. Blue outer layers with white inner layers seems to be the current trend, but people wear clothing of all colors and often import their clothes from elsewhere. They tend to prefer simple jewelry and the wealthy overall aren't known for showing off their wealth, though naturally some do.</p>
<p>While many of their buildings are made out of wood, a significant portion of limestone is used as well. </p>

@* <p><b>Real world comparison:</b> Overall architecture and clothing is most similar to China, but with Kalshanese and Vindralian influence.</p> *@


<h2 id="venlara">Venlara</h2>
<p>Sequestered within Verdant Valley, Venlara is often called The City of Flowers thanks to the many colorful flowers found all over the city. The people here revere nature above all else and have long worked to live in harmony with it, which is why animals, leshy, and other nature spirits are abundant within its borders. Perhaps this shouldn't come as a surprise, considering the city is largely ruled by a council of druids who follow a leader known as The Flower Monarch.</p>
<p>It's believed that Verdant Valley is blessed by nature spirits, which is why flowers and other plants grow in such abundance there.</p>

<h3>Sights & Fashions</h3>
<p>If someone were to describe Venlaran fashion in a single word, perhaps it would be "rustic," because even the wealthiest Venlarans tend to prefer practical clothes that were made out of natural materials found within Verdant Valley. While this can oftentimes mean furs from hunted animals, it also wouldn't be surprising to see a Venlaran wearing a cloak woven from leaves. Since Venlarans largely don't dye anything either, this has meant that earthy colors are quite common there.</p>
<p>Houses are traditionally square or cylindrical structures made out of wood. Their sloping roofs traditionally have a thin layer of dirt on top to grow grass, flowers, and other plants, while each building is surrounded by a garden. Some Venlarans have a rooftop garden, though this is a bit less common.</p>
<p>While some Venlaran gardeners cultivate foreign plants, plants native to Verdant Valley seem to thrive even without a gardener's help.</p>

