<h2 id="esalona">Esalona</h2>
<p>As the city-state bordering the Seishunese West, Esalona is largely responsible for defending the people of Merchant's Coast from the wilderness. While considered a pleasant place to live, only those with a Citizen's Mark - a magical tattoo signifying their citizenship in Esalona - are considered citizens and afforded the privileges that entails. Nonetheless, Esalonians will welcome any non-citizen with money within Esalona's walls and anyone without is welcomed outside of them.</p>

<h3>Sights & Fashions</h3>
<p>Within Esalona's walls, even the poorest citizen tends to prefer clean clothes that are brightly-colored and loose-fitting. Rich people who want to show off their wealth might wear gaudy jewelry or clothes of much higher quality material, such as silk. However, some particularly ostentatious individuals have been known to wear robes made of materials like gold or even dawnsilver.</p>
<p>This preference for cleanliness does seem to extend to more than fashion. While Esalonians can be quite forgiving of foreigners visiting their city, a person covered in filth can still expect to be prestidigitated at some point. They are preoccupied with cleanliness enough it's been said before that if a drunk were to piss in an alley late at night, it will have been cleaned up by the next morning.</p>
<p>But while things can seem overly sanitized within Esalona's walls, the sights outside of them are far more standard for what one might find elsewhere on Merchant's Coast. Not every farmer can be bothered to dye their clothes bright colors and non-citizens simply aren't held to the same standards citizens are, so while loose fitting robes are a bit of a staple throughout the city-state, the cleanliness and bright colors are unique to the city itself.</p>

